Anti-aging. 24 to 27 looks very different 😅 Same photographer, same location, 3 years later. 

24:
• Sun lover - destroying my skin any chance I got. Every crinkle and deficit is from the sun. BYE. 
• No sunscreen ever
• Awful injector at the time. Lips are over filled and migrated
• 0 structure to my face. No one told ya girl what she really needed
• NO FACIALS what!!!!!
• Pimple picker 🤮
• No microbladed brows yet oof
• Using poopy skincare brands: Tula, Dime… bunch of BS

27: ✨
• Professinal grade skincare all day everyday
• SUNSCREEN every single day. Yes in the winter. Yes inside. 
• Stopped tanning 100%. We do get the morning sun though
• Provider PICKY. I have gone to the best of the best to restructure this big ole face of mine @np_britt @glowup_by_diane 
• Facials, microneedling, laser treatments, chemical peels. You name it - I’ve done it
• Botox doesn’t change the quality of your skin. Invest in professional/medical grade products
• Blessed with the best mentor in the industry @wistlskin 
• Cut back on dairy, gluten & sugar plus my own personal food sensitives
• Bought me some BROWS!!! Best investment of my life @sabiskinstudio 

Y’all. We don’t have to be crusty if we don’t want to be. Stop listening to tik tok and IG influencers. They don’t know shit about fck.

If you need skincare advice - my website is linked in bio. I offer virtual consults and create home care routines for those who are serious about their skin 💕

Love,
Your honest Esthetician

#glowup #licensedesthetician #estheticianlife #antiaging #antiacne #facials #botox #dysport #lasertreatment #chemicalpeel #facialmassage #skincarejunkie #skincare #skinhealth

The comeback is greater than the setback sounds a lot like the dude who said money doesn’t buy happiness. 

Hip results: labral hip tear. No surprise & hip dysplasia. Super fuckin surprise.

My head is in all the places. Will my business survive with 2 months off. Do I need to hire an esthetician. How do I generate income when my business is all hands on. Is my crossfit journey officially over. Will this hip give me issues in the future. I REALLY don’t want invasive surgery. Thank goodness my chiropractor told me to get an MRI. All. The. Things. All the emotions. All the tears. All the fears.

At the end of the day I pray to God to close the doors that are meant to be closed, and open the doors that are meant to be open. If this is part of the plan then that’s it but mannnnn does this still crush my soul. 

CrossFit -Started with the 2015 open. Ending before the 2023 open. You will be missed 💔

8 years to get jacked. 1 month to lose it all lol

Hello body image issues - it’s been a minute 🙃

Most of you are aware I need stupid invasive hip surgery. Since finding out, I’ve completely stopped training. 1. because I’m in awful pain 2. I can’t really do anything. 3. I’m grieving lol

CrossFit was my only sport. It was my getaway from the madness of the world. It was the only hour I worked on myself. It took away my anorexia. It was the time to celebrate with friends on my wins and theirs. It was my outlet.

It’s weird watching myself shrink. Slowly walking back to square 1 has been a very weird journey… for really for anything in life.

For y’all struggling with whatever it may be - whether other people think it’s significant or not - you’re allowed to feel your feelings. We’re all going through our own versions of pain and discomfort in life. I won’t be sitting in my shit forever. Just for a lil bit.

Till next time Instagram ✌🏼

10 days post op thoughts…

I’m chillin.

My mental health is the best it’s been in MONTHS. I’m at so much peace now that the worst part is over with.

I never questioned why me. My question was why now. I’ve been seeking hip help since 2015 and I realized finding out now was because I am better equipped to handle this surgery present day. From years of crossfit, to friend support, to the physical mental and emotional support from Andrew. 2015 Alexis couldn’t do it. Today Alexis can.

My little strong arms are doing a great job of holding me up.

Apparently everyone but me knew I wouldn’t be able to move myself by myself so I’m extremely thankful to have my Andrew 🤍

I hate laying down lol. My back is like broken from all the laying, sitting slouched, not freely walking around.

Oh did we realize we take too much for granted.

I can’t wait to operate life at a slower pace after this. 

I miss my clients & business so much.

Not letting this surgery take me down.

🤘🏼

I have no idea what I did to deserve all the amazing people in my life but thank you, from the bottom of my heart, for taking care of me during this time in my life. 

From gifts, to checking in on me, to supporting my business, to Instagram messages, to FOOD deliveries, friends stopping by, the list goes far beyond the little time I get to talk on here. 

There are no words to explain this feeling of gratitude. It’s something I’ve truly never experienced before.

My people ARE THE BEST PEOPLE!!!!! Thank you all 🥹🫶🏼

Week 5 + 2 days 😍 We’re BIKING!!!

Every time my leg comes up and around I cringe. All of that scar tissue feels like barbed wire. My hip crease feels like it shouldn’t be allowed to move. I started sweating from anxiety. 🤣

Gaining inches on range of motion and LOVING LIFE. 6 week follow up is around the corner and I’m hoping if I slip my doc a hundo he’ll tell me no more crutches.

Waiting for my muscle groups that were cut up are taking the longest to heal. It takes a few times to convince myself to take a step. Or I guess lift my leg. BUT THIS IS TALLER THAN THE STEROID BOOK wooh!

Scar is looking great. Except the hip crease where the barbed wire is at. The scar even agreees that’s what’s in there.

Oh and laying on the scar feels like laying on a zipper… but with your skin zipped in it. Not a fan lol.

I’ve been barefoot for 5 weeks and I don’t want to go back to shoes.

PT is way more fun at home.

Week 16 🎁

Movement feels so much more normal. Still moving through massive amount of scar tissue but between my 5 million appointments, we’re getting there 😂🙌🏼

Scar tissue is weird. I get to a point where I am legit stuck and can’t move any further. I am DETERMINED to get my mobility back. Not into the parallel life.

For 4 months post op I am amazed. Every time I look back on how sad I was about doing this surgery kills me because it truly isn’t this horror story like everyone makes it out to be. Shits hard but what isn’t….

Take care of yourself. Especially when you have the option to do so ❤️

The weirdest year of my life.

Some INSANE ups and the hardest downs I’ve faced in a while.

📈 Expanded locations for my business, hired an estie bestie, upgraded 1 device and bought another, crazy cool things planned for the new year. my biz is my why. my people keep me going. All I want to do is provide the best for them. 

💪🏼 Last wza. Competed with that busted hip, knowing I was going to come home and face some gnarly news. 

🦿I truly do not know why because there are such worse things in life, but when I found out about my hip dysplasia, it crumbled me. The shock broke my brain and I spent 6 months depressed AF. It all stopped when I finally had my surgery. I absolutely love my surgeon. I legit never want surgery ever again though. 

🏡 Andrew and I were seconds away from moving to Florida lol. Not me trying to run away from my problems.

❤️ Speaking of Andrew… a year of relationship testers 😂 The amount of caregiving and caretaking is more than we ever thought we’d face idk probably ever??? Couldn’t do this life without him. He’s my better half. 

🎥 Super proud of @hillerfit2.0 His YouTube makes him thrive. Whether you’re a fan of it or not. He’s doing what makes him happy and isn’t that what we all strive for in life.

👯‍♀️ A year full of soooo many new friendships. Nourished current friendships. Shoutout to my bestie to sticking around throughout all my chaos @allie_a1217 

🪩 Really excited for a new year. New body, new mentality, new perspective, ready for any shit that comes my way. Ready to grow. Ready to heal. 

Thank you for being part of my weirdest year 🤘🏼

2024, pls be chill.
